<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06157242 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06157242 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  SAN-JOSE; SCHOOL; TAX; MONEY; PROGRAM; PLANNING  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  The board of the Oak Grove School District has decided how it will spend the$3.9 million from the parcel tax voters approved in March.;    Nearly 40percent of the money -- about $1.5 million -- will be used to soften the blowof budget cuts the district has already made or was bracing for. Among thecuts to be restored are library, custodial, counseling and English as a secondlanguage services.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  East Extra  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  SCHOOL DISTRICT TARGETS TAX FUNDS  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Also ran in EX4/7C  </MEMO><TEXT>     The remaining money will go for upkeep of heating, air conditioning andother ongoing maintenance expenses.;    In March, district voters passed a$68-a-year parcel tax by 73.6 percent. The tax will raise $3.9 million overthree years, which the district may use for general expenses.;    The districtwill be able to maintain restored services for the three-year life of theparcel tax. Next year, that means that instead of slicing $1.2 million fromits $47 million budget, it will only have to slice $700,000.;    While theMarch ballot measure specified how the parcel tax money could be spent, theboard's recent action stipulates how the money will be appropriated.;    Overthree years, the largest amount of money -- $1.1 million -- will go towardremedial services. Other big-ticket items include:;    (check) $660,000 formaintaining heating and air conditioning equipment.;    (check) $430,000 forrestoring cuts to English as a second language services next year.;    (check)$300,000 to improve the level of custodial service.;    (check) $258,000 tokeep library clerks at each of the district's 14 elementary schools for 3hours a week.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  MAYA SURYARAMAN, Mercury News Staff Writer  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910605  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Wednesday  </DAY><MONTH>  June  </MONTH><PG.COL>  3  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  257  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Wednesday June 5, 199100157242,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>